cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for texture recognition and understanding the nature of invariances captured by these representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of pre-images to understand categorical properties, which falls under the category of generative models and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a technique for attribute-based image manipulation, which could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of texture analysis and synthesis, which could be classified under cs.GR (Graphics).
